#  Get ready
  Phone to approve google requests and usb tethering if needed
  Make space for linux - disk management utility in windows. Shrink by 350000 on 1 TB drive.  Shrink windows partition.  Note partition #. (8).  Note any others you want to take over (5)
  Have >4 GB thumbdrive
  On Windows download iso.  flash using balenaEtcher
  Turn off bitlocker all drives
  Deauthorize tools like DVDfab, winxdvd, epubor in case can't get back
  Unplug second monitor, other usb's.  May leave mouse and keypad
  Create windows restore point
  Save github on windows

# insert iso usb
  F1 (rapid F12 on Lenovo laptop, F10 on HP
  Omen, F7 on little_guy) during boot.   Set boot order to USB.  *try or install ubuntu - normal installation - install updates (I tried minimal installation - lots of things didn't work right)
  Choose 'try or install Ubuntu.'  3 min to next step - will hear music
  Go through menus ~5 min
    Network - for next step
    Update to new version (green button)
    Full installation
    Custom:
      #p5 ext4 / all
      p5 swap        35 GB (larger than 32 GB Ram)
      p6 ext4 /      21 GB (recommended by web link)
      p7 ext4 /boot   2 GB (") large to hold both windows and pop
      p8 ext4 /home  balance GB
    daveg
  Wait ~12 min for install
    When prompted to reboot leave stick and wait until prompted to remove it
    I start with one letter password until end then change using instructions herein 
    
  If this won't 'install' (menu item grayed out, verify Fat32 and other stuff.  Then simply restart with the stick still in and try again.


#  Make EFI Boot Menu Work
# check this in Microsoft first
  you can confirm your Windows system is using UEFI mode by opening the System Information app and hecking the value of "BIOS Mode," which will be "UEFI" if in UEFI mode. Alternatively, you can se Disk Management to look for an "EFI System Partition" or in Command Prompt with the command reg uery HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Control /v PEFirmwareType to see if the DWORD value is 
  fast start disabled (Control Panel - Power)   CHECK!
  Bitlocker disabled  CHECK!
  Windows partition info
  /dev/nvme0n1p4 uuid 34B0CE20B0CDE906  NTFS 600 G B
  /dev/nvme0n1p1 1GB D18D-4F8F <----------------------------This is the EFI partition n1p1
  reboot.  In Bios change order so Pop-OS is at the top.  Save & exit & continue to boot
  
  # Map it to linux /boot instructions
  sudo apt install os-prober
  sudo os-prober
  # grab the output:  /dev/nvme0n1p1@/efi/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi
  sudo mount /dev/nvme0n1p1 /mnt
  sudo su
  cp -R /mnt/efi/Microsoft /boot/efi/EFI/Microsoft  # first version didn't have EFI
  ctrl-d to exit
  sudo nano /boot/efi/loader/loader.conf
  add 'timeout 8' to this file
  
  # create conf in entries folder for each os
  #  this was made automatically during install:  Pop_OS-current.conf
       title Pop!_OS
       linux /EFI/Pop_OS-c6774fc5-6e26-4eee-a040-36c5f2bcb792/vmlinuz.efi
       initrd /EFI/Pop_OS-c6774fc5-6e26-4eee-a040-36c5f2bcb792/initrd.img
       options root=UUID=c6774fc5-6e26-4eee-a040-36c5f2bcb792 ro quiet loglevel=0 systemd.show_status=false splash nvidia-drm.modeset=1 mem_sleep_default=deep
   # example from web for Windows: windows.conf  assumes standard location of windows boot manager (efi partition)
     windows.conf
      title Windows
      efi /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi


